            <title>[GROOVY-11384] STC: map property access within closure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-11384</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
void test(Map map) {
  println map.empty
  println map.with{ empty }
  println map.with{ delegate.empty }
  println map.with{ {-&amp;gt;owner.empty}() }
}

test( [:].withDefault{ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;entry&apos;&lt;/span&gt; } )
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When run as-is, the script prints &quot;entry entry entry entry&quot;.  With STC or SC enabled, Groovy 3 or 4 prints &quot;entry true true true&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
